===Proper noun===
'''Nile'''
{{wikipedia}}
# {{rivers}} Usually considered to be the longest river in the world, the Nile flows 6,677 km (4,150 miles) through [[Khartoum]] and [[Cairo]] in [[Africa]] into the [[Mediterranean Sea]].

